  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Life-Saving Shelter and Non-Food Items (NFI) in Support of Flood Affected Communities in Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving shelter and NFI assistance to the most vulnerable flood-affected families in Koji and Anambra states. IOM will distribute vouchers for shelter repair kits and NFI kits to 1,800 households based on the extent of damages to their houses and other vulnerability criteria. An estimated 10,800 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within five months.</narrative>
  </description>
